OPMODULO - "Operation - Modulo" ---- SPOJ
we define a function f(n) = (n mod 1) + (n mod 2) + (n mod 3) + ... + (n mod n), 
where n mod x denotes the remainder when dividing n by x. 
Rashad interests with integers n such that f(n) = f(n - 1), so he gave Mahmud two numbers L and R, 
and demands him to find the sum of all integers n such that L ≤ n ≤ R and f(n) = f(n - 1).

1--2--4--8--16---32... where f(n) = f(n-1).


#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    long long l, r; 
    cin >> l >> r; 
    long long ans = 0; 

    for (long long i = 1; i <= r; i *= 2) {
        if (i >= l) {
            ans += i; 
        }
    }

    cout << ans; 
}
